Community members are fuming over poor service delivery in the OR Tambo district municipality. They say government knows this area is always affected by storms yet it’s not prioritising them. eNCA reporter Nceba Ntlanganiso filed this report. #DStv403 MTHATHA - A Joint Ministerial task team has visited the Eastern Cape to assess the impact of floods on infrastructure. Water and Sanitation Minister Senzo Mchunu, Human Settlements Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi and Small Business Development Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams spent two days on community engagement in affected areas. Community members are fuming over poor service delivery in the OR Tambo district municipality. They say government knows this area is always affected by storms, yet it’s not prioritising them. * eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso reports.